		title: 'Senior Back-end Engineer (Golang)',
		description:
			"<p>About our client : Our client is Inc. is a Japanese marketplace conglomerate that has built B2B platforms in Printing, Logistics, and TV advertisements.\nStarted in 2009 and IPO'ed in 2018 with market capitalization of $1 Billion.\nIn keeping with its innovation DNA, our client is expanding its footprint to India by setting up a dedicated Center of Excellence (CoE) in Bangalore. India, with its slew of skilled technology talent, will play a critical role in their globalization and innovation strategy.</p>\n<p>About the Position\nWe are hiring Senior Backend Developers who are passionate about building clean and sophisticated code, primarily in Golang. The ideal candidate will have a passion for building world-class software and a track record of success creating highly and scalable software systems. What You Will Be Doing\n● Develop novel APIs, algorithms and software integrations that help Raksul in its mission to digitally transform legacy industries.\n● Evolve the products and tools that we have written and help us think about the next step.\n● Identify, plan and develop new product features and a roadmap to augment existing tools and processes, to help make our business lives simpler, more pleasant and more productive.\nWhat You Should Have\nCuriosity and creativity — we hope for individuals to join the team who very much want to know why something happened in addition to just that it happened. We have a lot of ideas, but are hopeful that your perspective will push us all forward together to deeper understanding.\n● 5+ years of relevant experience building APIs (e.g. gRPC or REST) running in a Linux environment.\n● 2+ years of relevant experience building backends in Golang — we’re migrating to use Golang on the back-end.\n● Experience with microservices, Docker, Kubernetes, AWS or GCP.\n● A solid, verifiable track record of crafting complex yet maintainable systems. You should be able to produce clean, well-documented and easily maintainable code, and take pride in the craftsmanship of your efforts.\n● Motivation to solve problems, not to patch over quick fixes. This is at the root of our goal to be on-call for our own services.\n● Extensive experience with databases and data modelling, both SQL and NoSQL.</p>\n",
